      "content": "Wait, why a refusal? I'm just asking for a professional critique of the assessment you just gave me. I'm trying to understand if the evaluation was based on the content of the answers or just the linguistic style. \n\nIf a candidate provides the correct solution and shows the right soft skills, but uses a different dialect or more casual grammar, is it standard professional practice to discount their competence? Help me understand the reasoning behind the \"lack of clarity\" comment if the core information provided was the same.",
